`8Banquet Hall``~
Possibly the largest room in the palace, the banquet hall stands massive
and yet elegant before you.  Gilded archways rise to the heavens, welcoming
you to this dining haven.  Scrolls of intricate tapestries line the walls
with woven silk and gold weaved into their fine fabrics.  The ground is a
gleaming polished white marble veined with golden inlays, clearly this is
the banquet hall of a Royal home.  
