#17507
`8Weaponsmith``~
This room is sweltering to say the least.  A group of sweating men
pound mercilessly upon an iron anvil as a pair of young apprentices
tend to the immense furnace in the corner of the room.  They pump
the billows quite frequently, sending sparks into the air and up the
chimney hanging overhead.  Beside each anvil is a trough of water
most likely for quenching the blades and armor as they are being
worked.  As each smith finishes a blade, he tosses to the side where
it is picked up and placed upon a rack beside hundreds of others.
~
Though the furnace's fire has been quelled, and the laborers have gone
home, the room is still quite hot.  The stone walls and earthen floor have
retained the heat making it nearly unbearable even in the night hours.  The
weapon racks have been cleared out, their contents most likely distributed
to the guards or sent out for export.  
~
